write a Python function to do a case insensitive sort of a list of strings
def case_insensitive_sort(list): 
    return sorted([x.lower() for x in list], key=str.lower)
```
This function takes a list as an argument and returns the same list with all its elements sorted in a case-insensitive manner using the `sorted()` method from the built-in library along with a lambda expression that converts each string to lowercase before sorting it.
